description._content: Catalog #: 09_01646 Title: First Lieutenant Harry Haw Special Collection Photo South Dakota Additional Information: Pilot Harry Haw in South Dakota, June 11 1920, Harry Haw served in the U.S. Army in the 514th Observation Squadron. He entered the U.S. Army in 1917 and became a First Lieutenant in 1930. He became a civilian Transport Pilot by 1930 and had logged 789 flying hours by 1934. he later became Principal of the Alice Birney school.
